Immediate past Oyo Governor Abiola Ajimobi is dead. He was said to have died of COVID-19 complications at First Cardiology Specialist Hospital, Lagos. He was 70. A source close to the former Governor told The Nation that Ajimobi breathed his last at about 4pm. Oyo House of Representatives member, Akin Alabi, also tweeted: “Forever in my heart.” Ajimobi was the first Oyo governor to win a second term in office. He governed between 2011 and 2019. Details shortly…